1020":null,"duedate":null,"customfield_12310250":null,"progress":{"progress":0,"total":0},"comment":{"comments":[{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12341166/comment/12405689","id":"12405689","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=amamment","name":"amamment","key":"amamment","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Arun Mammen Thomas","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"IMHO, bad reason to make the constants long.  All it takes is using any of:\n\nSystem.out.println(new Date(30L * 365 * DateUtils.MILLIS_IN_DAY));\nSystem.out.println(new Date(30 * 365L * DateUtils.MILLIS_IN_DAY));\nSystem.out.println(new Date(30L * 365L * DateUtils.MILLIS_IN_DAY));\n  or, best of all, \nSystem.out.println(new Date((long) 30 * 365 * DateUtils.MILLIS_IN_DAY));\n\n-AMT\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=amamment","name":"amamment","key":"amamment","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Arun Mammen Thomas","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2003-12-19T00:12:35.000+0000","updated":"2003-12-19T00:12:35.000+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12341166/comment/12405690","id":"12405690","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=n.metchev%40teamphone.com","name":"n.metchev@teamphone.com","key":"n.metchev@teamphone.com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Nikolay Metchev","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"IMHO, its a good reason to change because it introduces very subtle bugs which \nare tremendously difficult to track down. The fact that to fix the bug is an \neasy thing doesn't mean that finding the bug is easy. This will eliminate the \nbug altogether.\n\nIf you can think of a reason why it SHOULDN'T be long then let me know but if \nthere are not good reasons for keeping it an int then I guess it wont hurt!","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=n.metchev%40teamphone.com","name":"n.metchev@teamphone.com","key":"n.metchev@teamphone.com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Nikolay Metchev","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2003-12-19T00:21:25.000+0000","updated":"2003-12-19T00:21:25.000+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12341166/comment/12405691","id":"12405691","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=scolebourne%40joda.org","name":"scolebourne@joda.org","key":"scolebourne@joda.org","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.ap